From: thingino <thingino@opensensor>
Subject: [PATCH] mips/xburst/soc-t23: remove select TRACEPOINTS from CHIP_T23

The older ISVP SDK used by stock OEM T23 firmware (e.g. Ingenic "Immortal"
kernel, driver date 2024-1204) did not select TRACEPOINTS in CHIP_T23.
Without TRACEPOINTS, struct module is 0x118 bytes.  Our kernel's newer
SDK added "select TRACEPOINTS", making struct module 0x120 bytes.

Binary .ko files compiled against the older OEM SDK embed a 0x118-byte
struct module.  When the newer kernel tries to reference-count such a
module it reads module->refptr from offset 0x11c -- four bytes past the
end of the embedded struct -- finding zero and crashing in module_put:

  CPU 0 Unable to handle kernel paging request at virtual address 00000004
  epc == 800790e8  (module_put+0x2c)

The T23 platform does not use kernel tracepoints / ftrace at runtime.
Removing the select keeps CHIP_T23's struct module layout identical to
the OEM SDK, allowing pre-built binary .ko files to load safely.  All
in-tree modules built from source will be recompiled against the new
(smaller) struct layout and remain consistent.

Signed-off-by: thingino <thingino@opensensor>
--- a/arch/mips/xburst/soc-t23/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/mips/xburst/soc-t23/Kconfig
@@ -8,3 +8,2 @@
        bool "chip-t23"
-       select TRACEPOINTS
        select SYS_SUPPORTS_HIGHMEM
